+# Benchmark Comparison
+
+Run a controlled head-to-head between released OmniVoice and a candidate model
+using the same prompts, manifests, inference settings, and metric scripts.
+
+## What It Produces
+
+For each model and benchmark:
+
+- generated audio under `wavs/`
+- metric logs under `logs/`
+- `runtime_metrics.csv`
+- `runtime_metrics.summary.json`
+- `summary.json`
+
+For the full comparison:
+
+- `comparison/benchmark_summary.json`
+- `comparison/benchmark_summary.csv`
+- `comparison/primary_metric_scorecard.csv`
+- `comparison/report.md`
+
+If CloneEval is enabled, each model also gets:
+
+- `cloneval/metrics/results.csv`
+- `cloneval/metrics/aggregated_results.csv`
+- `cloneval/metrics/runtime_metrics.csv`
+- `cloneval/metrics/runtime_metrics.summary.json`
+
+## Quick Start
+
+```bash
+cd /Users/michael/Desktop/new_research/OmniVoice
+
+bash examples/run_benchmark_compare.sh \
+  /path/to/candidate_checkpoint \
+  exp/benchmark_compare \
+  /path/to/cloneval_test_list.jsonl
+```
+
+To download the standard evaluation assets first:
+
+```bash
+PREPARE_ASSETS=1 bash examples/run_benchmark_compare.sh \
+  /path/to/candidate_checkpoint
+```
+
+## Direct Python Entry Point
+
+```bash
+python -m omnivoice.scripts.benchmark_compare \
+  --baseline-model k2-fsa/OmniVoice \
+  --candidate-model /path/to/candidate_checkpoint \
+  --candidate-label CandidateModel \
+  --cloneval-test-list /path/to/cloneval_test_list.jsonl \
+  --prepare-assets
+```
+
+To compare released OmniVoice against an Aoede checkpoint, keep the baseline on
+the default OmniVoice modules and point the candidate at Aoede's bridge CLIs:
+
+```bash
+python -m omnivoice.scripts.benchmark_compare \
+  --baseline-model k2-fsa/OmniVoice \
+  --candidate-model /path/to/aoede/checkpoint.pt \
+  --candidate-label Aoede \
+  --candidate-infer-module aoede.eval.infer_batch \
+  --candidate-cloneval-module aoede.eval.cloneval_benchmark
+```
+
+## Notes
+
+- `fleurs` evaluation can run in a separate Python environment via
+  `--fleurs-python` if `omnilingual_asr` conflicts with the main environment.
+- The comparison report treats "better" as a benchmark result, not an
+  architectural claim.
+- Primary metric scorecard uses:
+  - CloneEval speaker similarity
+  - WER/CER
+  - SIM-o
+  - UTMOS where applicable
